			<h1 class="Unique">Pancake</h1>
			<p><h3>There are so many types of different pancakes, here a few that might make your lips watery</h3></p>
			<ol>
				<li><em>Apple Fritter Pancake</em></li>
				<li><em>Pumpkin Pancake</em></li>
				<li><em>Buttermilk Pancake</em></li>
				<li><em>Blueberry Pancake</em></li>
			</ol>
			<p><strong>I'm going to giving a recipe on how to make the blueberry pancake</strong></p>
			<h2 class="Unique">Blueberry Pancake</h2>
			<img src="images/pancake.jpeg" alt="A yummy pancake">
			<h3><em><p><ins class="inscription">Descripton</ins>: this pancake is golden and lightly crispy at the edges with a soft, tendre center. Blueberry pancakes with fresh blueberries are most definitely not just for any occassion. The baking powder in this pancake recipe is what makes them so fluffy!. its the yummmiest thing on earth.Its made up od milk, flour, baking powder, salt, milk.</em></p></h3>
			<h1 id="text">Ingredients</h1>
			<ul>
				<li><em>1<sup>1</sup>/<sub>4</sub> cups all-purpose flour</em></li>
				<li><em>1 tablespoon baking powder</em></li>
				<li><em>1<sup>1</sup>/<sub>4</sub> teaspoon white sugar</em></li>
				<li><em><sup>1</sup>/<sub>2</sub> teaspoon salt</em></li>
				<li><em>1 cup of milk</em></li>
				<li><em>1 egg</em></li>
				<li><em><sup>1</sup>/<sub>2</sub> tablespoon butter, melted</em></li>
				<li><em><sup>1</sup><sub>2</sub> cup frozen blueberries, thawed</em></li>
			</ul>
			<p><h1 id="Mine">Directions</h1></p>
			<ol>
				<li><em>Sift flour, baking powder, sugar, and sugar, and salt together in a bowl. Combine milk and egg in a small bowl. Stir egg mixture into flour mixture until just combined. Stir in melted butter, then fold in blueberries. Set aside for 1 hour.</em></li>
				<li><em>Heat a lightly oiled griddle or nonstick frying pan over medium-high heat.</em></li>
				<li><em>Pour or scoop the batter onto the hot griddle, using approximately <sup>1</sup>/<sub>4</sub> cup for each pancake; cook until bubbles appear on the surface, then flip and cook until golden brown on both sides. Serve hot.</em></li>
			</ol>
